Steps to set up the VM Instance

    1. Set up the Google Compute instance choosing the right amount of Vcpus(Choose 2 at this time)
       and RAM expanded to 16 Gigs, Under the disks option unselect the delete disk.... option,
       Select the number of GPUS required(Need to request for Quota first and then only can get GPU)

    2. Under the scripts put the scripts to download and install cuda, also do not forget to install
       cuDNN.

    3. Install anaconda and then install tensorflow gpu and keras

    4. To acess jupyter notebook, create a new firewell rule for the instance
       under Network tab in Google Cloud console. 
